com.locuslabs.sdk.location

Class FusedLocationProvider_IndoorAtlas_GooglePlayServices

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.locuslabs.sdk.location.FusedLocationProvider_IndoorAtlas_GooglePlayServices

  • public class FusedLocationProvider_IndoorAtlas_GooglePlayServices
extends java.lang.Object
    Fuses location data provided by IndoorAtlasAdapter and GooglePlayServicesLocationAdapter to provide an uninterrupted blue dot experience when the user walks from inside to outside and vice versa. Inside location is handled by IndoorAtlasAdapter and outside is handled by GooglePlayServicesLocationAdapter.

      • submitPositionSensorReading

        public void submitPositionSensorReading(java.lang.String source,
                                        LatLng latLng,
                                        double accuracy,
                                        java.lang.String floorId,
                                        java.lang.Double heading)
        Asynchronous location updates from IndoorAtlasAdapter and GooglePlayServicesLocationAdapter are transmitted here and "fused" together. The fusing algorithm is as follows:

        Given the location provider (source) is IndoorAtlasAdapter And the location is inside one of the venue's buildings Then do update the blue dot by calling PositioningSensorAlgorithm.External.recordPositionSensorReading(LatLng, Double, String, Double)

        Given the location provider (source) is GooglePlayServicesLocationAdapter And the location is outside one of the venue's buildings (i.e. if Venue.buildingForLatLng(LatLng, Venue.OnBuildingForLatLngListener) gives us a null) Then do not update the blue dot

        Parameters:
        source - either IndoorAtlasAdapter and GooglePlayServicesLocationAdapter
        latLng - the lat/lng submitted by the source
        accuracy - the source's self-reported error radius around the latLng in meters
        floorId - which floor the source thinks the user is on
        heading - the direction the source thinks the user is heading (aka "bearing")

      • acceptIndoorOutdoorClassification

        public static boolean acceptIndoorOutdoorClassification(java.lang.String classification,
                                                        long classificationTimestamp,
                                                        java.lang.String source,
                                                        java.util.Deque<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.Long,java.lang.String>> pastClassificationsFromSource)
        Determines whether a location provider's most recent classification of indoor/outdoor should be accepted based on the following criteria: 1-Source: IndoorAtlas is good for indoor and GooglePlayServices is good for outdoor 2-Consistency: the source has reported the same classification at least 3 times in a row 3-Durability: the consistency spans at least 5 minutes
        Parameters:
        classification - the most recent classification ("indoor" or "outdoor")
        classificationTimestamp - the time of the most recent classification
        source - which location provider reported the classification
        pastClassificationsFromSource - a FIFO queue of past classifications from the source where the key is the timestamp and the value is the classification at that time. It's a Deque to guarantee its iterator returns values in FIFO order ("When a deque is used as a queue, FIFO (First-In-First-Out) behavior results." See Deque documentation)
        Returns:
